                                              Display Response





## Architecture Description

The AI Workspace follows a modular client-side architecture. Users interact with the application through a React-based frontend consisting of a chat interface, conversation sidebar, and settings panel. User actions are managed through React Context and Hooks, which maintain the application's state.

The AI Service Layer acts as an abstraction between the user interface and AI providers. During development, a mock AI service generates sample responses. The architecture is designed to allow seamless integration with external providers such as OpenAI, Google Gemini, Claude, Groq, or OpenRouter.

Conversation history is stored locally using the browser's Local Storage, ensuring persistence across sessions without requiring a backend database.

This modular architecture improves scalability, maintainability, and future extensibility while keeping the user interface independent of AI provider implementations.
